where kij, i, j = 1, 2, 3 are constants. We notice that the equilibria for Models I and II are (S, u1, u2) = (0, 0, 0), (S, u1, u2) = (K , 0, 0) and those described in Eq. (2).

Remark 2. The corresponding system associated with the system (5) was considered in [17] when ki,j ̸= 0 for i = j and ki,j = 0 for i ̸= j. The results obtained in [17] suggest that, if there is no cross-diffusion included in system (1), then diffusion-driven instability can
not happen and the zip bifurcation phenomenon is sustainable regardless of the self diffusion coefficients. The maim aim of this paper
is to show that the zip bifurcation is sustainable for system (10) and that diffusion-driven instability emerges for system (12). We also
establish that the conditions k11, k22, k33, k12, k13 > 0 and k21, k31, k23, k32 < 0, are sufficient for the occurrence of the diffusion-driven
instability for system (12).

