Proposition 1. If K > a1 + 2λ, then all equilibria on LK are unstable.

Now, if u∗ is an unstable equilibrium for the flow of (1) then u∗ is also an unstable homogeneous equilibrium for the flow of (11), since the subspace of the functions independent of x is invariant for the flow of (11). The next theorem shows that if u∗ is stable for the flow of (1) then u∗ may not be stable for the flow of (11).
